TCS’s Chandrasekaran Says Strategic Capability Key for Purchases

-- B y   Y u d i t h   H o
-- 
2011-08-05T10:35:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/tcs-s-chandrasekaran-says-strategic-capability-key-for-purchases.html
N. Chandrasekaran, chief executive
officer of  Tata Consultancy Services Ltd. (TCS) , comments on the
company’s search for acquisition targets in the U.S. and Japan.
He spoke in an interview today in  Singapore .  “We look at Japan, we look at the U.S. If there’s a
strategic capability, like health-care segment, then we’re very
interested.  “We have a lot of cash -- more than $2 billion. We’re
looking for acquisitions for strategic capability. It’s not just
for growth, because we have very good organic growth.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yudith Ho in Singapore at 
